$interpreted: Fredrica: That's strange. From what I remember, Atlas should be really cold. Why are there water holes everywhere?
Jerome: General, Atlas' climate has gotten warmer recently.
Jerome: The frozen areas have gradually shrunk in size, causing this to occur...
Fredrica: This sucks. My shoes are covered in mud~
Fredrica: If it weren't for vacation, I'd never come to this god-forsaken place...
Nigel: If you don't want to be here, then go the hell home!
Jerome: A demihuman? Wait, wait, we have no ill intentions...
Fredrica: Hey, horny boy, I'm warning you.
Fredrica: I'm not feeling too good right now, so it'd be best if you didn't get in our way~
Jerome: General! Please, be careful with your words...
Nigel: Encroaching on others' land without thought, and yet you are still this arrogant! Watch me drive you from Atlas!
Lio: W-Wait, Nigel!
Nigel: Lio, Leah? What are you doing...
Lio: These are emissaries of Angel's, they're not bad people!
Nigel: Angelia...?
Nigel: Lio, please explain.
Nigel: Hmph, the grand princess. Not surprised she won't leave us be...
Lio: Huh?
Nigel: ...Nothing.
Nigel: Fine...I'm aware of why you're here.
Nigel: We are reconstructing our homeland and are lacking various resources. The Queen's goodwill...I shall accept respectfully.
Fredrica: No need to thank us~
Fredrica: Horn boy, is there any place to take a rest? If we head back now, we'll have to camp out in the wilderness~
Nigel: ...What's wrong with this woman...
Lio: Nigel, can they stay with us? They must be tired from lugging all those materials...
Lio: And I...want to stay with you for a while.
Nigel: Let me be clear. Though I accept the benefits of humans, that doesn't mean the oppression that demihumans have long-endured will go away.
Nigel: We have already...lost too many.
Leah: ...Cin...
Nigel: ......
Jerome: Mr. Nigel, we didn't mean...
Nigel: Perhaps you've no ill intent, but everyone is exhausted and we must deal with the raids of human bandits.
Nigel: I can't leave you at risk of attack.
Fredrica: ...A group of bandits?
Nigel: Initially, those rats didn't show their faces in this region. Recently, they've had their eyes on us; always harassing us at night.
Nigel: Several people have already been injured.
Leah: Everyone...
Jerome: ...No news of this has been heard within the kingdom. It is the responsibility of the ruler of the land to maintain peace...
Nigel: Forget it. I've never counted on humans.
Nigel: Since Atlas is the demihumans' home, we will fight these bandits back and protect our land.
Nigel: ...What?
Fredrica: Just look at you. Those circles under your eyes~ Plus, your coarse skin...and you've got more than a few pimples~
Nigel: Wh-What did you say!?
Fredrica: The quality of your skin and sleep are intricately related.
Fredrica: There must not be many demihumans who can fight. You probably do rotating patrols...right?
Nigel: ...Uh...
Fredrica: Aigh~ This is exactly what the enemy wants.
Fredrica: Am I right, handsome?
Jerome: Indeed. I'm guessing that the bandits don't want a straight forward battle, but are relying on guerilla warfare.
Jerome: After weakening your mental and physical energy, they'll invade when you're completely exhausted...
Nigel: ...We are aware...
Lio: Nigel, Eve is...
Nigel: Relax, she's fine...but since I'm commanding the troops, Yamitsuki has been taking on most of the patrol work.
Nigel: I've been over-exerting myself, haven't taken a rest in days...
Leah: Why...
Nigel: ...If...I can think of a better way...
Fredrica: ......Nigel...
？？？: AH!! Help!!
Lio: Is that a woman's voice?
Jerome: Could it be the bandits Nigel spoke of?
Female Villager: H-Help! These bandits, they...
Nigel: ...Hey, she's human too. You ain't gonna let her go?
Nigel: More shameless than I thought. Bastards.
Vicious Bandit: Eh? Disgusting demihuman, quick sticking your head in our business!
Nigel: Humans taking from humans doesn't concern us. Unfortunately, this is our home, Atlas.
Nigel: ──If you want to plunder and pillage, go somewhere else!
Scheming Bandit: Hilarious. This region is our territory!
Scheming Bandit: It was you lowly demihumans who barged the kingdom without permission, taking all the valuables for yourselves!
Fredrica: Ya~This is just a simple misunderstanding...
Fredrica: It's forgivable that you weren't aware, but the queen has agreed that they live here.
Fredrica: It's completely legal~
Scheming Bandit: L-Legal? But they're lowly demihumans...
Fredrica: Don't be like that...handsome~!
Jerome: Yes, ma'am! Lio, Leah, please step back!
Vicious Bandit: What...what are you gonna do?
Fredrica: Nothing. We just want to get something straight...
Fredrica: Are you the bastards who've been making that girl named Yamitsuki work too hard and worrying this boy?
Fredrica: You rotten apples, getting in the way of love...
Fredrica: ...you deserve an ass-whooping!
Vicious Bandit: N-No! They're too strong! Retreat!
Fredrica: Walking back has to be inconvenient for you. Lucky for you, I'm in a good mood. I'll send you back!
Scheming Bandit: O-Ouch!!
Lio: General Lucien is awesome!
Fredrica: Little bandits like these aren't worthy to be called my opponents.
Fredrica: Okay, you're fine. Head back now.
Female Villager: T-Thank you!
Fredrica: What's the matter, horn boy?
Fredrica: After all this, you're still suspicious of us?
Nigel: ...Forget it.
Nigel: Seeing Lio's face, I'll let you stay. But I won't let you screw with my comrades.
Nigel: If you get out of line...don't blame me if I kick you out early.
Fredrica: Sounds about right. Handsome, let's go~
Lio: Sis, let's go~
Lio: ...Sis?
Lio: Wah! What are you doing?
Leah: Lio...I...I'm a genius.
Lio: ...Eh?
Leah: I can help Nigel and everyone. Plus, we don't have to waste our vacation...
Leah: Hehe, I've got the perfect plan!
Lio: ...What are you talking about...sis?
